column9: Type of soap is your outcome variable
Clean up the data set and document your actions
Summarize the data after clean up
Create at least four sets of visuals to describe the dataset and shed light to questions such as (you are not limited with these insights, Fell free to create your own questions/answers):
Which type of soap, payment type, location dominate the dataset, if any
Are customers who live in a certain region tend to by certain types of soap?
Do the payment method differs based on age, location, and/or quantity?
One set must be box-plots and another set must be scatter plots
Conduct KNN to predict the type of soap for a new customer who is 55 years old living in an urban area, buying 3 units of soap and paying by credit card
All codes need to be documented. A self-contained file (word of pdf) that includes all the codes, comments, plots and other outputs must be submitted.
Binning the ages into age groups
Bonus of 10 points will be given to creativity - documentation
